title: Three spacewalks completed across two days on two space stations
summary: In low Earth orbit (LEO) this week, NASA, Roscosmos, and the China National Space Administration (CNSA) performed spacewalks outside humankind’s two permanently-crewed space stations.

title: Boeing reorganizes defense unit, Kay Sears to lead space and launch business
summary: Boeing is reorganizing its defense and space business, a sector of the company that last month reported nearly $3 billion in losses in the third quarter.

title: NASA's Perseverance Rover Investigates Intriguing Martian Bedrock
summary: Exploring a sediment-rich location in this Mars delta offers tantalizing opportunities for the six-wheeler’s science team.

title: Precious Payload partners with Arkisys, Rocket Factory Augsburg to market payload slots and launches
summary: Precious Payload has announced partnerships with a pair of companies to market payload slots and launches on its online satellite launch marketplace.
